NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So if it goes 1@H-P-3@C-P-3@S, that establishes a game force, and is a control bid in spades looking for slam. But if it goes 1@H-P-3@C-P-3@D, that is a game try (the partnership is not yet committed to play 4@H), not a control bid.|
PG| ***** 100 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|However, on Board 4, the 2@C bid already established the game force. And the 2@H rebid by responder showed 3-card heart support. So the partnership is already committed to at least 4@H and may want to bid slam. Therefore all new suits below 4@H are control bids looking for slam.|
