^B@2^*BBarry Rigal: ^*N|cp||at|When East opens 1@S, there is no remotely sensible bid that South can make. The choices, such as they are, are to double, which of course is take-out, promising short Spades, or to overcall 1NT to show a balanced hand of 15(+)-18 points. Both of these bids are gross misdescriptions, and it is much more sensible to pass, and hope to get a chance to bid later on.|
